Element Description: The degree to which this data set could be made publicly-available, regardless of whether it has been made available. Choices: Public (Asset is or could be made publicly available to all without restrictions), Restricted Public (Asset is available under certain use restrictions), or Non-Public (Asset is not available to members of the public).
Human-readable description (e.g. an abstract) with sufficient detail to enable a user to quickly understand whether the asset is of interest.
Internal field for linking data assets to configured "data types".
Internal unique identifier field for the data asset.
Internal field for tracking the timestamp at which this data asset  entry was last updated in the database.
Internal field for linking data assets to configured "projects".
Internal field for tracking the source platform of the data asset.
Internal field for tracking the data asset type.
A unique identifier for the asset or API as maintained within an Agency catalog or database.
Tags (or keywords) that help users discover the data asset.
Most recent date on which the asset was changed, updated or modified.
Human-readable name of the data asset. Must be in plain English and include sufficient detail to facilitate search and discovery.
Internal field for tracking the total download count of the data asset from their source platform.
Internal field for tracking the number of page views within the last 30 days on the data asset's source platform.
Internal field for tracking the total page views on the data asset's source platform.
URL link to the data asset.
